s guided continuously by the Ad=\r\nesha of Sri Krishna. He would literally hear the voice of Krishna speaking =\r\nto him, instructing him to do this or do that. Krishna was his Guru, the Di=\r\nvine Mother beyond all manifestation, was his destination. Anyway, my point=\r\n is not to try and sell Sri Aurobindo&#39;s perspective of spirituality. I have=\r\n benefited from it, but not necessary that everyone else will also benefit.=\r\n There are so many sadgurus who have come to India, each with their unique =\r\nperspectives and ideas and philosophies. Each must individually try and fin=\r\nd whose ideas gel properly with our mental and emotional makeup, and help u=\r\ns to progress on the path. \n&gt; \n&gt; Though I now have a very deep respect for =\r\nSri Aurobindo, I maintain a safe distance from both his critics and his bli=\r\nnd-admirers. Both of them, in my opinion, have misunderstood the depth of h=\r\nis teachings. Both their love and their hatred is a function of their own e=\r\ngos, like it was mine 3 years ago, and not based on any genuine understandi=\r\nng or appreciation. In spirituality, no Sadguru can be understood accuratel=\r\ny or even slightly without sincere sadhana. \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; &lt;&lt; \n&gt; Disclaimer---- M=\r\ny thinking is \n&gt; very different due to Darshan and=C2 Grace of Divine Mothe=\r\nr & Divine \n&gt; Lord. Nobody should feel unhappy If I do not agree or follow =\r\nthe \n&gt; leader.Thanks.&gt;&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; I at-least will never feel unhappy if you dis=\r\nagree. There are \n&gt; many saints, many philosophies, many paths, not everyon=\r\ne is bound to \n&gt; like every path.=C2=A0 Disagreement is perfectly ok. Becau=\r\nse someone \n&gt; disagrees with me or those whom I agree with, does not mean I=\r\n like him \n&gt; any less. I try to keep my=C2=A0 emotional side (where respect=\r\n, love, \n&gt; dislike, hatred, anger, passions exist) separate from my thinkin=\r\ng mind. \n&gt; It is very much possible, through practice, for a man to disasso=\r\nciate \n&gt; his rational-mind from the emotional-mind. So have no fears that y=\r\nour \n&gt; disagreement is going to make me like you any less or any more. \n&gt; \n=\r\n&gt; The problem with the emotional part of our being is that it jumps up at a=\r\nppearances, running ahead to grasp the truth rather than waiting patiently =\r\nfor the truth to arrive in all its aspects and dimensions, and in the proce=\r\nss it distorts the truth and then reacts to that distorted image. For examp=\r\nle, recently in some social forums I posted a comment that I found the Tant=\r\nrik Adwaitha far more appealing than Sri Adi Shankara&#39;s Adwaitha, though th=\r\ne Adwaitha of Adi Shankara has many hard-selling supporters. Immediately so=\r\nme friends of mine on Twitter and otherwise, jumped to the false conclusion=\r\n that I have disrespected Adi Shankara, and tried best to make me &quot;see the =\r\ntruth&quot; by such grandiose statements that=C2=A0 Shankara is the &#39;final word&#39;=\r\n on Adwaitha and everything else must be necessarily lesser. Or that I was =\r\nmaking an egoistic denouncement. Both of which are million light-years away=\r\n from the truth. That Sri Adi Shankara was a special Vibhuti \n&gt;=A0 (manifes=\r\ntation) of God, that much I am certain. His compositions are so brilliant t=\r\nhat it can&#39;t be sufficiently appreciated in words. Yet, I have equally no q=\r\nualms in rejecting his philosophy. And because I am not bound to accept his=\r\n philosophy, does not mean I respect or love him any less than any other gr=\r\neat saint.=C2=A0 \n&gt; \n&gt; If you disrespect a man, and specially a saint, and =\r\nthen start disliking him too with a passion, you are creating strong negati=\r\nve karmas. But if you can disagree with someone without losing respect or l=\r\nove for the person, in an objective manner, you reap very little karmic eff=\r\nects. That is why Lord Krishna too advices us to become more detached in li=\r\nfe. \n&gt; \n&gt; In conclusion, Narasimha is totally correct. Many things cannot b=\r\ne sufficiently expressed in words without causing some distortion. \n&gt; \n&gt; -R=\r\negards \n&gt; =C2 Rajarshi \n&gt; \n&gt; =C2=A0 \n&gt; \n&gt; awaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE m=\r\nAmabuddhayah | \n&gt; param bhAwamajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24] \n&gt; \n&gt; \n=\r\n&gt; ________________________________ \n&gt;=A0 From: Laxmi Narayan &lt;shrijishrihar=\r\ni@...&gt; \n&gt; To: &quot; vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt; vedic-wisdom@...=\r\nm&gt; \n&gt; Sent: Thursday, 11 October 2012 12:21 AM \n&gt; Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdo=\r\nm] Re: A thought \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; =C2=A0 \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; =C2=A0 \n&gt; Dear Rajarshi Bhai, \n&gt; =\r\nHow are you doing? About 200 hundred years ago, a man made a theory of crea=\r\ntion in France. When Napolean asked where is God in it, the guy said, do no=\r\nt talk about God. It makes things complicated. \n&gt; So is there a place for D=\r\nivine Mother and Her Love or Grace or Protection in your theory. Is=C2 this=\r\n intermediate zone as you say is created by Her and part of Her creation=C2=\r\n or by=C2 somebody else.=C2=A0 Does=C2 She needs some visa to go there if s=\r\nhe is=C2 not the Creater.=C2 As you say all higher deity are there but less=\r\n in ability. Does the deities have even less =C2 ability on earth plane. \n&gt;=\r\n =C2=A0 \n&gt; I am sure this is not your theory. You have taken it from yogi A=\r\nurobindo. Many times when certain person reach a stage in their spiritual p=\r\nath, others think whatever this guy is uttering is=C2 complete truth, when =\r\nin fact it is=C2 far from truth. Once=C2 I saw in a article that Aurobindo =\r\nsaid that Divine Lord who spoke Gita completely forgot it after few minutes=\r\n or so. I could not believe what I was reading. Then my respect for this yo=\r\ngi went down the drain. \n&gt; =C2=A0 \n&gt; Divine Mother, Her Love, Her Grace Her=\r\n Protection and