cessfully done, this sublte for=\r\nmation of the deity which exists in the subtle plane, has a life of its own=\r\n. It can then guide the sadhaka through the path and eventually, one day le=\r\nad him/her to the real abode of the deity which is the karana-jagat (beyond=\r\n this astral plane). If a person is able to awaken his/her Kundalini shakti=\r\n, and make it\n identify/create such an astral formation of the deity, it be=\r\ncomes an even more powerful force. It is, from our limited human perspectiv=\r\ne, as much a powerful entity as we may imagine, yet it is often not the act=\r\nual Deity yet. Exactly the same thing has been described by Sri Vimalananda=\r\n in the Aghora books, if you read carefully.=C2&nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; Whe=\r\nn a sadhaka has been able to associate with such an astral formation of the=\r\n deity, it can guide the sadhaka along the path provided the sadhaka also i=\r\ns trying to work hard and sincerely to reach the causal planes (the real sp=\r\niritual planes of existence where the real force of the Deity originates). =\r\nThe difference, if you ask, between this astral formation of the deity and =\r\nthe real deity is that, the former is neither bound nor capable by itself o=\r\nf causing a complete and total transformation of the average human nature w=\r\nithout a proactive help of the sadhaka. Whereas, if one reaches the plane o=\r\nf the\n Great Gods, which is where the real deity exists, one cannot avoid b=\r\neing transformed in mind, emotions, body etc. And what kind of a transforma=\r\ntion will it be? One that will reflect to the world as a greater and genuin=\r\ne humility, sense of deep surrender to the Divine at ALL time and unfailing=\r\nly, a complete withdrawal of lower nature of man - lust,&nbsp; anger, &lt;br&gt;&=\r\ngt;&nbsp; jealousy, greed, covetousness - an abiding peace, calm, detachmen=\r\nt, mental-illumination, genuine compassion, a widening of the consciousness=\r\n. Such an individual, even if he/she just sits down next to another person,=\r\n will exude a silent strong peace and unselfish love which will automatical=\r\nly calm the minds and disturbed emotions of lesser mortals ETC. THAT is the=\r\n authentic, unhindered flow of the Divine Power of any of the great deities=\r\n. This comes even if one deity is properly realized in the causal planes of=\r\n existence. But the astral formation of the same deity, which is created\n b=\r\ny the force of our own pranashakti or Kundalini as the case maybe, is often=\r\n not capable of affecting this kind of a total transformation in a sadhaka.=\r\n That is why it is limited. It is not limited because it can&#39;t=C2&nbsp; get=\r\n me a better job or a nice pay hike or cure some diseases or bring me fame =\r\nor any such material benefit if I so ask of it - the astral formations of&n=\r\nbsp; the deities &lt;br&gt;&gt;&nbsp; can very easily do all these things in the =\r\nphysical world - but it is limited because it cannot by itself give you the=\r\n must authentic and persistent spirituality of the higher planes, the one a=\r\nim and destination of all genuine sadhana. &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; Since this ast=\r\nral plane is the way it is, therefore it&#39;s extremely important to keep acti=\r\nvely working on ourselves to increase detachment, objectivity, genuine inte=\r\nrnal surrender (when that happens one accepts all life-situations without t=\r\nhe slightest grudge), humility, control of anger, lust, jealousy\n etc. (all=\r\n that is universally accepted as spiritual qualities). For unless these cha=\r\nnges are affected at least to some degree in the mind and emotions of the s=\r\nadhaka, one is simply not ready to reach the higher planes of God and benef=\r\nit from them spiritually. Moreover, at every stage of spiritual evolution t=\r\nhere is a gap between experience and realization. Only repeated experiences=\r\n *may* lead to realization. One off experiences create a force no doubt, bu=