ail, for 15 days Swami Viveka=\r\nnanda would appear before him daily and instruct him on the various layers =\r\nof the mind, which he was not aware of till then. Swami Vivekananda had alr=\r\neady left his physical body by then. It was in the writings of Sri Aurobind=\r\no that he mentioned about the left and right hemisphere of the brain and th=\r\neir difference in functionality, and their connection to spirituality, abou=\r\nt 30 years before medical science confirmed the same. &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; Rig=\r\nht from getting out of jail, to settling in Pondicherry, to pushing his own=\r\n spiritual experiences further into states of Sahaja (which he describes in=\r\n different terminology), etc etc, he was guided continuously by the Adesha =\r\nof Sri Krishna. He would\n literally hear the voice of Krishna speaking to h=\r\nim, instructing him to do this or do that. Krishna was his Guru, the Divine=\r\n Mother beyond all manifestation, was his destination. Anyway, my point is =\r\nnot to try and sell Sri Aurobindo&#39;s perspective of spirituality. I have ben=\r\nefited from it, but not necessary that everyone else will also benefit. The=\r\nre are so many sadgurus who have come to India, each with their unique pers=\r\npectives and ideas and philosophies. Each must individually try and find wh=\r\nose ideas gel properly with our mental and emotional makeup, and help us to=\r\n progress on the path. &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; Though I now have a very deep resp=\r\nect for Sri Aurobindo, I maintain a safe distance from both his critics and=\r\n his blind-admirers. Both of them, in my opinion, have misunderstood the de=\r\npth of his teachings. Both their love and their hatred is a function of the=\r\nir own egos, like it was mine 3 years ago, and not based on any genuine und=\r\nerstanding or\n appreciation. In spirituality, no Sadguru can be understood =\r\naccurately or even slightly without sincere sadhana. &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;=\r