 necessarily lesser. Or that I was\n =\r\nmaking an egoistic denouncement. Both of which are million light-years away=\r\n from the truth. That Sri Adi Shankara was a special Vibhuti &lt;br&gt;&gt;&nbsp;=\r\n (manifestation) of God, that much I am certain. His compositions are so br=\r\nilliant that it can&#39;t be sufficiently appreciated in words. Yet, I have equ=\r\nally no qualms in rejecting his philosophy. And because I am not bound to a=\r\nccept his philosophy, does not mean I respect or love him any less than any=\r\n other great saint.=C2&nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; If you disrespect a man, and=\r\n specially a saint, and then start disliking him too with a passion, you ar=\r\ne creating strong negative karmas. But if you can disagree with someone wit=\r\nhout losing respect or love for the person, in an objective manner, you rea=\r\np very little karmic effects. That is why Lord Krishna too advices us to be=\r\ncome more detached in life. &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; In conclusion, Narasimha is t=\r\notally correct. Many things cannot be sufficiently expressed in\n words with=\r\nout causing some distortion. &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; -Regards &lt;br&gt;&gt; =C2 Rajars=\r\nhi &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; =C2&nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; awaktam wyaktimApannam man=\r\nyantE mAmabuddhayah | &lt;br&gt;&gt; param bhAwamajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[=\r\n7:24] &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; ________________________________ &lt;br&gt;&gt;&=\r\nnbsp; From: Laxmi Narayan &lt;shrijishrihari@...&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; To: &quot; vedic-w=\r\nisdom@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt; vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; Sent:=\r\n Thursday, 11 October 2012 12:21 AM &lt;br&gt;&gt; Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Re=\r\n: A thought &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; =C2&nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;&gt;=\r\n =C2&nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&gt; Dear Rajarshi Bhai, &lt;br&gt;&gt; How are you doing? About 2=\r\n00 hundred year